dvertising for a <abbr title=\"personal assistant\">PA</abbr> and health and safety training for your <abbr title=\"personal assistant\">PA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<h3>What you can&rsquo;t use the money for</h3>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t use the money to pay for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>any care you get from a relative who lives with you</li>\n  <li>any care provided by social services</li>\n  <li>maintaining your home or adapting your home</li>\n  <li>gardening</li>\n  <li>bills</li>\n  <li>private hospitals, residential care or holidays</li>\n  <li>petrol, taxi fares and travel expenses</li>\n  <li>childcare</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>On-going support and reviews of <abbr title=\"Independent Living Fund\">ILF</abbr> payments</h2>\n\n<p>An independent assessor will visit you every 2 years to make sure you’re still getting the right level of payments and you’re keeping the right records.</p>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Independent Living Fund\">ILF</abbr> will write to you when you are due for a visit to tell you which assessor will contact you and explain what will happen. Your social worker (if you have one) will need to be there when the assessor visits.</p>\n\n<p>They will check that you&rsquo;re getting the right amount of care and look at the records you&rsquo;ve been keeping. They will also ask you about the care you pay for, the money you have and the benefits you get.</p>\n\n<h2>If your care costs change</h2>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Independent Living Fund\">ILF</abbr> will not normally be able to meet increases in the amount of care you need. When reviewing your <abbr title=\"Independent Living Fund\">ILF</abbr> payments, the assessor will consider if the amount of money you currently receive is sufficient.</p>\n\n<p>If your care arrangements change and you need more money to pay for your care, contact your <a href=\"/apply-needs-assessment-social-services\" title=\"Apply for a needs assessment by social services\">local authority</a> and ask them to reassess your care needs. They may be able to offer you extra help.</p>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Independent Living Fund\">ILF</abbr> will consider giving you more money if you need to pay for employer costs. Examples of these include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Criminal Records Bureau (CRB) checks</li>\n  <li>health and safety training</li>\n  <li>National Insurance contributions</li>\n  <li>Statutory Sick Pay</li>\n  <li>Advertising for a <abbr title=\"personal assistant\">PA</abbr></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>If you&rsquo;re unhappy about a decision</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re unhappy about a decision, you can contact the <abbr title=\"Independent Living Fund\">ILF</abbr> and ask them to look at it again. This is called a ‘decision review’. If you&rsquo;re unhappy with the service you receive you can make a complaint. If you&rsquo;re still not happy you can appeal.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Independent Living Fund Helpline</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Telephone:</strong> 0845 601 8815 or 0115 9450 700  <br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0845 601 8816</p>\n\n<p>Monday to Thursday, 9am to 4:30pm and Friday, 9am and 4pm<br />\n(closed Wednesdays, 10:30am to 11:30am)  </p>\n\n<p>Email: <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#102;&#117;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#064;&#105;&#108;&#102;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#102;&#117;&#110;&#100;&#115;&#064;&#105;&#108;&#102;&#046;&#111;&#114;&#103;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nEquinox House\n<br />Island Business Quarter\n<br />City Link\n<br />Nottingham\n<br />NG2 4LA\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>If your circumstances change</h2>\n\n<p>Tell the <abbr title=\"Independent Living Fund\">ILF</abbr> straight away if your circumstances change. A change in your circumstances may affect the amount of money you get from the <abbr title=\"Independent Living Fund\">ILF</abbr>. Some examples of the changes you need to report include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>changes in the support you get from s