 Allowance if both the following apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you reach State Pension age</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re not in regular employment</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>How you&rsquo;re paid</h2>\n\n<p>All benefits, pensions and allowances are paid <a href=\"/how-to-have-your-benefits-paid\" title=\"how to have your benefits paid\">into an account</a>, eg your bank account.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/reduced-earnings-allowance/eligibility","slug":"eligibility","order":3,"title":"Eligibility","body":"<p>You could get Reduced Earnings Allowance if you&rsquo;re suffering from an illness or disability caused by a work-related accident or disease that happened before 1 October 1990.</p>\n\n<p>You must also meet all of the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your level of disability is assessed to be at least 1% </li>\n  <li>you can&rsquo;t return to your regular occupation </li>\n  <li>you can&rsquo;t do other work with the same level of earnings as your regular occupation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Going abroad</h2>\n\n<p>If you leave the UK to live permanently outside the European Economic Area (<abbr title=\"European Economic Area\">EEA</abbr>), you won&rsquo;t be able to get Reduced Earnings Allowance.</p>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"European Economic Area\">EEA</abbr> includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>all <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://europa.eu/about-eu/countries/index_en.htm\" title=\"countries in the EU\">countries in the <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr></a></li>\n  <li>Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For temporary visits, you can usually claim for the first 3 months of your stay. </p>\n\n<p>This can be longer in special circumstances - check with the International Pensions Centre to see if you qualify.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>International Pensions Centre</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0191 218 7777  <br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0191 218 7021  <br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Your circumstan