 mother was vaccinated against one of the diseases in the list while she was pregnant</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;ve been in close physical contact with someone who&rsquo;s had an oral vaccine against poliomyelitis </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>What counts as &lsquo;severely disabled&rsquo;</h2>\n\n<p>Disablement is worked out as a percentage, and &lsquo;severe disablement&rsquo; means at least 60% disabled. </p>\n\n<p>This could be a mental or physical disablement and will be based on medical evidence from the doctors or hospitals involved in your treatment.</p>\n\n<h2>When and where the vaccination must have taken place</h2>\n\n<p>You must normally have been vaccinated before your 18th birthday unless the vaccination was during an outbreak of disease in the UK or the Isle of Man, or it was against:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>poliomyelitis</li>\n  <li>rubella</li>\n  <li>Meningococcal Group C</li>\n  <li>human papillomavirus</li>\n  <li>pandemic influenza A (H1N1) 2009 (swine flu)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The vaccination must have been given in the UK or the Isle of Man, unless you were vaccinated as part of Armed Forces medical treatment.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/vaccine-damage-payment/how-to-claim","slug":"how-to-claim","order":4,"title":"How to claim","body":"<p>Apply by filling out a claim form. If you&rsquo;re under 18, your parent or guardian should claim on your behalf.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dwp.gov.uk/advisers/claimforms/vadla_print.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Vaccine Damage Payment claim form' (PDF, 166KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Vaccine Damage Payment claim form’ (PDF, 166KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Send it to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nVaccine Damage Payments Unit\n<br />Palatine House  \n<br />Lancaster Road   \n<br />Preston PR1 1HB\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<p>You can also contact the Vaccine Damage Payments Unit to ask for a claim form:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Vaccine Da