ory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr>)</a>. Some employers have their own sick pay scheme instead.</p>\n\n<p>If you still can&rsquo;t work after 28 weeks, or you can&rsquo;t get Statutory Sick Pay, you can apply for <a href=\"/employment-support-allowance\" title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">Employment and Support Allowance</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Time off from work should not be recorded as an &lsquo;absence from work&rsquo; if you&rsquo;re waiting for your employer to put reasonable adjustments in place.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Check your <a href=\"/employment-status\" title=\"employment status\">employment status</a> if you’re not sure whether you’re an employee or not.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Dismissals and redundancy</h2>\n\n<p>Your employer can&rsquo;t dismiss you just because you&rsquo;ve become disabled. </p>\n\n<p>You can be dismissed if your disability means you can&rsquo;t do your job even with reasonable adjustments. </p>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t be selected for <a href=\"/redundant-your-rights\" title=\"redundancy your rights\">redundancy</a> just because you&rsquo;re disabled.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>For advice about work issues, talk to <a href=\"http://www.acas.org.uk/index.aspx?articleid=1410\" title=\"ACAS\" rel=\"external\"><abbr title=\"the Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service\">ACAS</abbr></a> (the Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service), <a href=\"http://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/index/getadvice.htm\" title=\"Citizens Advice\" rel=\"external\">Citizens Advice</a> or your trade union representative.</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:16:32+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Carers and disability benefits","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/benefits%2Fdisability.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes Disability Living Allowance, Carer's Allowance and Employment and Support Allowance","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.go